                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d718">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.102S/1234: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1"
                            type="from">Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-09-06T17:00:00+08:00"
                            >September 6, 1932—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 6—6:44 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1074. My 1058, September 3, 1 p.m. Following from <persName
                        corresp="frus1932v03#p_CES1">Cunningham</persName>: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“September 6, 9 a.m. Legation’s July 30, 2 [<hi rend="italic">1?</hi>]
                                p.m.,<note n="3" xml:id="d718fn3">See telegram No. 961, August 16,
                                1932, 7 p.m., from the Minister in China, <ref target="#pg_635">p.
                                    635</ref>.</note> paragraph 1, last sentence. Notwithstanding
                            various complications which have arisen as reported in my August 31 [<hi
                                rend="italic">13?</hi>], 10 a.m., and previous telegrams it is
                            assumed that foregoing instruction is still in effect.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>To which I have replied: “Views expressed in my July 30, 1 p.m., still
                    stand.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
